author_ssm: Jasmine Soliman and Jonathan Burr, with assistance from Emily Broad for Akkasah: Center for Photography NYUAD
unittitle_ssm: Royal Flying Corps - Egypt in the 1910s
abstract_ssm: This photograph album contains a collection of photographs of scenes in Egypt compiled by an unidentified Royal Flying Corps member in 1916–19. The photographer was quite possibly assigned to the Number 14 Squadron that assisted T. E. Lawrence in the Arab Revolt (1916–18). The album also yields first-hand snapshot images of World War I aircraft, including several crashed aeroplanes. Interesting is the photograph of a destroyed tank, since only a few of these were deployed in the Middle East during WWI The final 58 photographs show the compiler's home life in Great Britain.
